On the main repository page (https://bitbucket.org/user/repo), on the "Recent commits" area, the *date commited* column displays

//3 minutes left//

shouldn&#x27;t this be

//3 minutes ago//?

As far as I can tell the Wiki syntax does not allow text to have different colors than the default (black). However, this would be helpful in many situations.

I would like to see something like:\\
{{{\\
[color=red]This text is red[/red]\\
}}}

http://wiki.amxmodx.org/Introduction_to_SourcePawn

SourcePawn is the language used for Sourcemod, which is used to modify and extend games based on Valve&#x27;s Source engine.

It looks mostly like C.  The biggest difference is that variable declarations look different.

{{{\\
#!c\\
new intvar;\\
new Float:floatvar;\\
decl String:uninitializedString[30];\\
}}}
